1016
00:51:15,016 --> 00:51:17,358
Also, hire someone with physical training

1017
00:51:17,438 --> 00:51:19,500
to do your capture, like a professional dancer

1018
00:51:19,540 --> 00:51:20,341
or a martial artist,

1019
00:51:20,921 --> 00:51:23,003
or someone who's just very good with their hands.

1020
00:51:23,103 --> 00:51:25,525
It's easier for them to repeat choreography,

1021
00:51:25,605 --> 00:51:26,586
make graceful motions,

1022
00:51:26,986 --> 00:51:28,948
and they probably won't get tired very quickly.

1023
00:51:30,599 --> 00:51:32,500
Performance in VR is just so much more important

1024
00:51:32,520 --> 00:51:34,421
because every little head and hand movement,

1025
00:51:34,461 --> 00:51:37,103
scene one to one, it's very easy for the performance

1026
00:51:37,123 --> 00:51:39,124
to have no energy or flow.

1027
00:51:39,264 --> 00:51:42,426
So get a dancer or martial artist, makes a big difference.

1028
00:51:44,647 --> 00:51:46,187
And make a free cam for your VR game.

1029
00:51:46,668 --> 00:51:48,149
More shot variety makes the footage

1030
00:51:48,209 --> 00:51:49,549
just much more fun to watch.

1031
00:51:50,150 --> 00:51:51,970
So whatever you can do to create more shots

1032
00:51:51,991 --> 00:51:54,672
that aren't from the first person's perspective, do it.

1033
00:51:54,692 --> 00:51:56,133
