1092
00:54:55,822 --> 00:55:00,325
Okay, so in summary, think about capture early.

1093
00:55:00,345 --> 00:55:02,466
The sooner you think about how your game looks

1094
00:55:02,506 --> 00:55:03,387
in video, the better.

1095
00:55:04,027 --> 00:55:05,088
Helps you market your game,

1096
00:55:05,408 --> 00:55:07,069
and it might even help you with the game's design.

1097
00:55:09,111 --> 00:55:10,752
Watch films with great cinematography,

1098
00:55:10,892 --> 00:55:12,593
good visual flow, and camera moves.

1099
00:55:13,293 --> 00:55:15,975
Not saying your shots have to rival Hollywood directors,

1100
00:55:16,035 --> 00:55:19,377
but might inspire you to, or give you some good ideas.

1101
00:55:21,983 --> 00:55:23,244
Watch films with great framing.

1102
00:55:23,704 --> 00:55:24,624
There are a lot of great directors,

1103
00:55:24,705 --> 00:55:26,245
but just start with Kurosawa.

1104
00:55:26,566 --> 00:55:28,527
Like, just watch all the Kurosawa films.

1105
00:55:29,047 --> 00:55:29,567
It's amazing.

1106
00:55:31,609 --> 00:55:33,170
Watch films with well-shot action.

1107
00:55:33,190 --> 00:55:37,172
You know, good blocking, good spatial awareness in editing.

1108
00:55:37,232 --> 00:55:38,593
So watch Jackie Chan films.

1109
00:55:38,653 --> 00:55:41,235
Watch Yuen Woo-Ping choreographed films.

1110
00:55:41,335 --> 00:55:44,376
John Wick, Edgar Wright films, Guillermo del Toro.

1111
00:55:46,890 --> 00:55:49,651
Give yourself the tools to create great shots.

1112
00:55:50,151 --> 00:55:52,491
Without good tools, just making it harder for everyone.

1113
00:55:54,732 --> 00:55:56,012
Think of yourself as a puppeteer.

1114
00:55:56,032 --> 00:55:59,173
Again, game capture isn't simply playing,

1115
00:55:59,213 --> 00:56:00,194
it's a performance.

1116
00:56:02,474 --> 00:56:03,494
Capture with intention.

1117
00:56:04,095 --> 00:56:05,835
Think about what the intent of each shot is

1118
00:56:06,295 --> 00:56:08,396
and how to best achieve that visually.

1119
00:56:10,842 --> 00:56:12,543
And really, simplify your shots.

1120
00:56:12,884 --> 00:56:14,485
It makes them much more readable.

1121
00:56:14,665 --> 00:56:17,026
So strip away anything inessential.

1122
00:56:17,426 --> 00:56:21,109
And I'll leave you with some good advice from Jackie Chan.

1123
00:56:21,889 --> 00:56:26,252
The most difficult thing is when I throw the fan

